    "body": "I could use some guidance with this issue.\r\n\r\nHere's what I've determined so far: `send`, `receive` and `@browse` will focus\r\nthe input component the first time they run, but after that they won't\r\ntrigger the `basic-text-input` `:on-focus` event.\r\n\r\nInterestingly, tapping the `/location` command will focus text input and bring\r\nup the keyboard again, allowing one subsequent use of `send`, `receive` or `@browse`\r\nto show the keyboard.\r\n\r\nThe major difference between `/location` and the wallet commands or `@browse` is\r\nthat `/location` is a reagent component while the wallet commands are js react.\r\n\r\nI'm not sure if that has anything to do with the problem though. Any insight from\r\nthe clojure team, or some next steps to debug?\r\n\r\n[video example here](https://drive.google.com/open?id=0B-eUTMyNoFvPcjJobUdETnRsQjg)",
